'This table contains information about petty cash.
It will link to CLOSE_DAY via department, machine and reference number';

COMMENT ON TABLE CLOSE_DAY_VOUCHERS IS
'This table contains information about vouchers (Gift certificate and store credit) used and iussued.
Used are from a payment made in EasyPOS (ART=16 in table TRANSAKTIONER)';

COMMENT ON TABLE CREATEUPDATE_DISCOUNTS IS
'This table will contain information about discount to new items or items which need update
Sinse the database currently can hold 0, 1, 2 or 3 discount per head item or variant, we will onlu allow sequence to be 1, 2 or 3.';

COMMENT ON TABLE CREATEUPDATE_ITEM IS
'This table will hold information when Create, Update or CreateUpdate API is called.
This is the master.
Table CREATEUPDATE_ITEMS will hold eash incomming item.
This tale contains a UUID which uniquely identifies the incomming items, and this is what is used to let caller ask "status" of the operation
GOAL is what we need to reach. PROCESS is what we are at.
BATCH_STATUS tells in which stae we are.
LOG_ contains detailed informtion about then operation
START_TIME tells us when we started.
UPDATE_TIME is time of last update or end time if we are done';

COMMENT ON TABLE CREATEUPDATE_ITEMS IS
'This table will contain whatever was send via the API to Create, Update or CreateUpdate products in the database.
Recods has a foreign key (MASTER_ID) which points to ID in CREATEUPDATE_ITEM.
There are sub tables belonging to this.
These are:
 - CREATEUPDATE_PRICES
 - CREATEUPDATE_DISCOUNTS_HEADITEM (If not present coming soon)
 - CREATEUPDATE_DISCOUNTS_VARIANT (If not present coming soon)
Some values are mandatory for a create. Other are mandatory for updates.
See swagger definitions for more information';

COMMENT ON TABLE CREATEUPDATE_PRICES IS
'This table is a subtable for CREATEUPDATE_ITEMS
This table will hold information like cost-, salesprice, VAT and min.stock etc
This applies for either:
 - The currency set
 - The country set
 - The departments set
 - None - which means all departments in all currency
if none is set, it applies for all, and if currency departments are pressent, prices will calculates "as is" from the currency defined in the system
More information in swagger';

COMMENT ON TABLE SETTLEMENTS IS
'This table will hold information about settlements made in the program.
The data will come via a trigger on table TRANSAKTIONER.
In that table records aith ART=5 is inserted, which is settlements.';



